{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778905035890,"sessionID":"ses_1d10260feffeTFmAt6ufe0Ie5q","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"functions.write:15","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"Changes committed in PR #<NN>.\n\nThis PR addresses the two partonomy revisions requested:\n\n1. **UBERON:0001043 (esophagus)** — Removed the `located_in` some `thoracic cavity` axiom, since the esophagus has cervical and abdominal parts (at least in humans) and therefore is not wholly located in the thoracic cavity.\n\n2. **UBERON:0035539 (esophageal artery)** — Replaced `branching part of` some `thoracic aorta` with `connecting branch of` some `thoracic aorta`, consistent with how similar arterial relationships are modeled elsewhere in UBERON.\n\nPlease review and let me know if any further adjustments are needed.\n","filePath":"/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"ISSUE_COMMENTS.md","time":{"start":1778905035885,"end":1778905035889}},"id":"prt_e2f009a48001Z2UbFSsUi0hl25","sessionID":"ses_1d10260feffeTFmAt6ufe0Ie5q","messageID":"msg_e2f008e89001VuoY58i9IFWyme"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778905053266,"sessionID":"ses_1d10260feffeTFmAt6ufe0Ie5q","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"functions.write:16","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"## Summary of Changes\n\nThis PR revises the partonomy of `esophagus` and `esophageal artery` to better reflect anatomy and to align with existing relationship patterns in UBERON.\n\n### 1. UBERON:0001043 — esophagus\n**Removed:** `relationship: located_in UBERON:0002224 ! thoracic cavity`\n\n**Rationale:** The esophagus has cervical, thoracic, and abdominal parts (at least in humans). Asserting that the entire esophagus is `located_in` the thoracic cavity is therefore anatomically inaccurate. No replacement axiom was added; the existing `part_of` relationships and regional subdivision terms already capture the anatomy appropriately.\n\n### 2. UBERON:0035539 — esophageal artery\n**Changed:** `relationship: branching_part_of UBERON:0001515 {source=\"FMA\"} ! thoracic aorta`  \n**To:** `relationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001515 {source=\"FMA\"} ! thoracic aorta`\n\n**Rationale:** `connecting_branch_of` is the standard relationship type used throughout UBERON for arteries that arise from a larger vessel and supply a specific organ or structure. This change brings the esophageal artery into consistency with hundreds of other arterial terms already modeled with this relationship.\n\n### Checklist\n- [x] Checked out relevant terms using `obo-checkout.pl`\n- [x] Verified `connecting_branch_of` is an existing, widely used relationship in UBERON\n- [x] Confirmed the `located_in` axiom is the only thoracic-cavity-related location assertion on the esophagus term\n- [x] Made minimal, targeted edits to the checked-out term files\n- [x] Checked terms back in with `obo-checkin.pl`\n- [x] Reviewed diff to ensure only intended changes were applied\n- [x] Committed changes to `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo`\n\nSigned-off-by: @dragon-ai-agent\n","filePath":"/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"PR_COMMENTS.md","time":{"start":1778905053258,"end":1778905053264}},"id":"prt_e2f00b4f6001RZxRDbQaSPYcBw","sessionID":"ses_1d10260feffeTFmAt6ufe0Ie5q","messageID":"msg_e2f008e89001VuoY58i9IFWyme"}}
